Can you use your lemmas to shorten the proofs of the existing lemmas?

A general style comment: spaces after `rw` and `simp`:
```suggestion
    rw [Finset.prod_insert his, Nat.coprime_mul_iff_left, ih, Finset.forall_mem_insert]
```

```suggestion
  Finset.cons_induction_on t (by simp) fun i s his ih  by
    rw [Finset.prod_cons, Nat.coprime_mul_iff_right, ih, Finset.forall_mem_cons]
```
avoids the need for `DecidableEq `

```suggestion
    Coprime ( i in t, s i) x   i  t,  Coprime (s i) x :=
```
and below
Could you move these two lemmas below and shorten their proofs?
I think using `alias` would be appropriate here, and perhaps renaming to `Coprime.prod_left` etc for constructor dot notation.
I redefined using alias and renamed to `Coprime.prod_left` and `Coprime.prod_right`.
